content.text:
I'll analyze both structures in the main target image and provide assembly instructions for each.

Left Structure (House-like):
- Has 4 layers
- Made of 8 blocks: 2 blue cubes at base, 1 yellow horizontal block, 1 red cube, 1 blue cube, 1 green horizontal block, 1 orange triangular roof piece

Right Structure (Doorway/Gate):
- Has 3 layers
- Made of 6 blocks: 2 yellow vertical blocks as sides, 2 green horizontal blocks (top and bottom), 1 red block in the middle

Assembly Instructions:

For Left Structure:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1 (blue cube)
    Step2: Move block with index 4 (blue cube)
    Step3: Move block with index 7 (yellow horizontal)
    Step4: Move block with index 2 (red cube)
    Step5: Move block with index 1 (blue cube)
    Step6: Move block with index 5 (green horizontal)
    Step7: Move block with index 13 (orange triangle roof)
}

For Right Structure:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 5 (green horizontal)
    Step2: Move block with index 9 (yellow vertical)
    Step3: Move block with index 10 (yellow vertical)
    Step4: Move block with index 2 (red cube)
    Step5: Move block with index 5 (green horizontal)
}
